<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Sophie Monk has been forced to confirm she's alive after rumours swept the internet that she had died.</p>

<p>The fake story shared to a Facebook page titled 'R.I.P Sophie Monk' claimed the 40-year-old star had passed away on Tuesday and it attracted almost one million 'likes'. </p>

<p>KIIS FM hosts Kyle Sandilands and Jackie O Henderson contacted Sophie live on air on Thursday, and the Love Island host confirmed she is alive and well.</p>

<p>'I'm still here!' Sophie Monk (pictured) has been forced to deny she's DIED after a fake story started trending on social media on Thursday</p>

<p>'Sophie this is Kyle and Jackie O, we just rang for proof of life,' Kyle informed the 40-year-old.</p>

<p>Sophie said: 'You two are the only ones who have called me. No one else bothered to call me. Thank you so much!'</p>

<p>She went on to explain the fake article was published in Los Angeles and ' it received one million likes on Facebook.'</p>

<p>Sophie also revealed: 'They did a survey and 75 per cent of people said they enjoyed the death hoax.'</p>

<p>Fake story: KIIS FM hosts Kyle Sandilands and Jackie O Henderson contacted Sophie live on air on Thursday, and the Love Island host confirmed she is alive and well</p>

<p>She also shared a photo of the article to her Instagram stories on Thursday and told her followers she was 'still here'.</p>

<p>'2020's been tough but I'm still here,' she wrote alongside a laughing emoji.</p>

<p>On Tuesday, a Facebook page titled 'R.I.P Sophie Monk' claimed the Australian media personality had passed away.</p>

<p>Alive and well: She also shared a photo of the article to her Instagram stories on Thursday and told her followers she was 'still here'</p>

<p>'At about 11am ET on Tuesday (September 22, 2020) our beloved singer Sophie Monk passed away. Sophie Monk was born on November 12, 1979 in London,'the post read.</p>

<p>'She will be missed but not forgotten. Please show your sympathy and condolences by commenting on and liking this page,' it ended.</p>

<p>The Facebook page and posts have since been deleted.</p>

<p>Hoax: On Tuesday, a Facebook page titled 'R.I.P Sophie Monk' claimed the Australian personality had passed away</p>
